			<div class="breadcrumb">You are here: <a href="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/" title="View Home">Home</a> / <a href="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/category/recipes/" title="View all items in Recipes">Recipes</a> / Split Pea Ham and Potato Soup</div>	<div class="post-11546 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-recipes category-soups">

				<h1 class="entry-title">Split Pea Ham and Potato Soup</h1>
		
		<div class="post-info"><span class="date published time" title="2011-10-03T20:50:31+00:00">October 3, 2011</span>  <span class="post-comments"><a href="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/2011/10/split-pea-ham-and-potato-soup/#comments">90 Comments</a></span> </div>		<div class="entry-content">
			<p><a href="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Split-Pea-Ham-and-Potato-Soup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11547" title="Split Pea Ham and Potato Soup" src="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Split-Pea-Ham-and-Potato-Soup.jpg" alt="Split Pea Ham and Potato Soup" width="500" height="375" /></a></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Ingredients</strong></span></p>
<p>20 oz dried split peas<br />
6 cups water<br />
2 15-oz cans chicken broth<br />
1 lb smoked ham cubes or cut up ham steak<br />
1 large carrot, chopped<br />
1 small onion, chopped<br />
1 large potato, cut into 1/4-inch pieces<br />
4 Tbsp butter<br />
2 tsp salt<br />
1 tsp pepper</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Directions</strong></span></p>
<p>Combine all ingredients in stockpot. Cover and heat to boiling.</p>
<p>Reduce heat and simmer until the peas take on a smooth texture. (usually about 1 1/2 hours)</p>
<p><a href="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Split-Pea-soup.jpg"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-11549" title="Split Pea soup" src="http://www.anutinanutshell.com/wp-content/uploads/2011/09/Split-Pea-soup.jpg" alt="Split Pea soup" width="500" height="351" /></a></p>
